title: enpera
body:
When hair poofs out above a [[scarf]] (or similar apparel, like [[headphones around neck]]).

It is named after the fins near the tip of the mantle of the Japanese flying [[squid]], which in turn takes its name from Emperor [[Napoleon Bonaparte]] due to the fins' resemblance to his [[bicorne]].

Users on pixiv largely refer to this look as えんぺら (enpera), but on other sites such as Nicoseiga the term マフモコ (mafumoko) may also be used. This phrase in particular is a contraction of two words: マフラー (muffler, [[scarf]]) and モコ (moko, onomatopoeia for soft and fluffy).

h4. External links

title: highly_responsive_to_prayers
body:
東方靈異伝 ("Touhou Rei'iden") ~ The Highly Responsive to Prayers ("Unusual Spirit Transmissions of the East")

First game of the [[Touhou]] series, released for NEC PC-9801 on November 1996. Part of the [[Touhou (PC-98)|Touhou PC-98]] era of games.

Someone has wrecked the [[Hakurei Shrine]], an important gateway between [[Gensokyo]], Jigoku (World of Hell) and Makai (World of Demons). Its [[miko]], [[Hakurei Reimu (PC-98)|]], chooses between entering Makai and Jigoku to find out who destroyed her shrine, leading her either to an [[sariel (touhou)|angel of death]] or a [[konngara (touhou)|jealous spirit]].

title: elly_(touhou)
body:
A [i][[Touhou]][/i] character that appears as the Stage 3 boss in [i][[Lotus Land Story]][/i].

The gatekeeper of Mugenkan and subordinate of [[Kazami Yuuka]]. Wields a scythe and telekinetically throws giant floor tiles at her opponents. Her whereabouts after the events of [i]Lotus Land Story[/i] are unknown, but in lieu of any canon information, it's believed that she still serves Yuuka, and now guards the [[Garden of the Sun]] instead.

Her imagery is apparently meant to invoke an ankou, a Celtic spirit of death.

Her notable quote is this: "I couldn't help it! I couldn't help it!"

Best remembered for her stage theme, [[Bad Apple!!]].

h4. External links

title: garand_thumb
body: M1 Thumb/Garand Thumb refers to an injury sustained by the operator of an [[m1 garand|M1 Garand rifle]] in the process of pushing the en-bloc clip down until it engages. It is caused when the bolt stop slips out of engagement, allowing the bolt to slam forward with the operator's thumb still in the clip/mag well. This causes the thumb to be trapped and can sometimes require moderate medical attention to treat, such as stitches, depending on the angle and strength of the bolt as it hits the thumb.

title: okazaki_yumemi
body:
Okazaki Yumemi (岡崎夢美) is the canonical final boss of the third [[Touhou]] game 東方夢時空 〜 The Phantasmagoria of Dim.Dream ("canonical" because it's a dueling shooter, so everyone fights everyone anyway). 

An eighteen-year-old university probability physics professor from the future who got shunned by society for believing in magic, she comes to Gensokyo to capture its specimens and prove her theory is right. A genius even by the future's high standards, she's the creator of the Probability Space Hypervessel - something not only capable of travel between time and space, but also of ripping through the Great Hakurei Barrier.

Yumemi's outfit and appearance is primarily red: her eyes, hair, vest, skirt, [i]and[/i] her cape are all red.  Even the bow on her white blouse is red.  Commonly, she will be represented by a red cross motif in reference to her in-game attacks; or strawberries, in reference to her theme music, [i]Strawberry Crisis!![/i]

She will often be seen with her assistant and fellow scientist, [[Kitashirakawa Chiyuri]].

h4. See also

* Touhou Wiki: http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Yumemi_Okazaki

title: sheikah
body:
A human tribe appearing in the [i][[the legend of zelda|Legend of Zelda]][/i] franchise. While the tribe was introduced in [i][[the legend of zelda: ocarina of time|Ocarina of Time]][/i], few Sheikah appeared in the franchise outside of [[Impa]]'s incarnations up until [i][[the_legend_of_zelda:_breath_of_the_wild|Breath of the Wild]][/i], where they are practically the most important race in the game's backstory, being responsible for all of the high technology in the game.

They basically look just like Hylians, except with white hair and (traditionally) red eyes; [i]Breath of the Wild[/i] Sheikahs do have a wider range of eye colors. They also live somewhat longer than Hylians: Impa, Purah and Robbie are in their 120s.

Some of their members have split to form the [[Yiga Clan]] in the [i]Breath of the Wild[/i] timeline.

title: gundam_combat
body:
A short-lived [[Gundam]] card game released between 1996 and 1997. The game featured SD [[mobile suit]]s, with the first release featuring mobile suits from [[Gundam wing|Wing]], [[after war Gundam X|X]], [[G Gundam|G]] and [[Mobile suit Gundam|MSG]]. The second release added mobile suits from [[Gundam 08th Ms team|08th MS Team]], [[Gundam 0080|0080]], [[Gundam 0083|0083]], [[zeta Gundam|Zeta]], [[Gundam ZZ|ZZ]], [[char's Counterattack|CCA]], [[victory Gundam|Victory]], and [[Gundam wing Endless waltz|Wing EW]].

While the game has been largely forgotten, it's somewhat notable for featuring a variety of new original variants for the mobile suits featured in the first set . 

Official card illustrations are by [[Taiga Hiroyuki]].

title: andean_condor
body:
Latin: [i]Vultur gryphus[/i]

This large black South American [[vulture]] features a ruff of white feathers surrounding the base of the neck and large white patches on the [[wings]]. The head and neck are nearly featherless, and are a dull red or grey. In the male, there is a wattle on the neck and a distinctive large comb or caruncle on the crown of the head. 

The Andean condor features in several South American national coat-of-arms.

h4. See also

title: condor
body:
Condors are a description of two species of New World [[vulture|vultures]], the California condor and the [[Andean condor]]. They are in the Cathartidae family but are classified into different genus.

The adult plumage is uniformly black, with the exception of a frill of white feathers nearly surrounding the base of the neck, which are meticulously kept clean. As an adaptation for hygiene, the condor's head and neck have few feathers, which exposes the skin to the sterilizing effects of dehydration and solar ultraviolet light at high altitudes. This skin is pink or grey depending on species and mood.

They have flattened heads, which in the male is crowned with a caruncle or comb, while the skin of the neck lies in folds, forming a wattle. Due to the extent of bare skin on the head which extends below the nostril, the beak can appear relatively small.

Condors are frequent subjects of worship or reverence in indigenous cultures.

h4. See also

title: heracles_(housamo)
body:
[[Tokyo Afterschool Summoners]] character.
Designed by [[nikism|Sousuke]]

Transient from the world of Olympus. He is a hero born from a divine connection to lightning and a political scheme from System Olympus that magnifies belief. He is an extraordinarily strong warrior and has wandered many battlefields due to an oracle granted to him, but he also has a past of destroying everything dear to him due to a madness instilled into him. To atone for that crime, a new oracle was handed down that made him a slave for the span of three years and forced him into a role of absolute obedience to his master's orders. Brandished as a show of his superior's power with no thought of freedom and a healthy work environment, Heracles was exhausted in mind and body and sought the days without battle within his mind. Perhaps due to that, it seems like his current state as a slave feels more restful to him than his time as a bloodsoaked warrior. He's sympathetic to those who are given absurd abuse by their superiors and environment like him.

title: frigate_bird
body:
Frigatebirds are a family of seabirds called Fregatidae which are found across all tropical and subtropical oceans.

They have predominantly black plumage, long, deeply forked tails and long hooked bills. Females have white underbellies and males have a distinctive red gular pouch, which they inflate during the breeding season to attract females.

title: african_elephant
body:
The African elephant ([i]Loxodonta[/i]) is a genus comprising two living elephant species, the African bush elephant ([i]L. africana[/i]) and the smaller African forest elephant ([i]L. cyclotis[/i]). Both are social herbivores with grey skin, but differ in the size and color of their [[tusks]] and in the shape and size of their ears and skulls.

African [[elephant]]s are distributed in Sub-Saharan [[Africa]], where they inhabit Sahelian scrubland and arid regions, tropical rainforests, mopane and miombo woodlands.

They are larger and have larger ears than [[Indian elephant|Indian elephants]].

title: cuttlefish
body:
Cuttlefish or cuttles are marine molluscs of the order Sepiida. They belong to the class [[Cephalopod|]]a, which also includes [[squid]], [[octopus|]]es, and [[nautilus (animal)|]]es.

Cuttlefish have large, W-shaped pupils, eight arms, and two [[tentacles]] furnished with denticulated suckers, with which they secure their prey.

title: trilobite
body:
Trilobites are a group of extinct marine arthropods. The first appearance of trilobites occurred in the Early Cambrian period (521 million years ago), and they disappeared in the end-Permian mass extinction about 252 million years ago.

Trilobites are characterized by a cephalon (head), thorax (body) and pygidium (posterior), and form a calcitic exoskeleton that is easily preserved as a [[fossil]].

title: samantha_(admiral_bahroo)
body:
Samantha is a female mascot character for the streamer Admiral Bahroo.  Depending on her design she may have [[brown hair|brown]] to [[orange hair]] or [[black hair|black]] & [[white hair|white]] [[two-tone hair]] with [[blue eyes]]. As of her second design she has sported clothing with a [[panda]] theme.

She is commonly depicted with Bahroo's other mascot, the small panda [[Umeru (admiral bahroo)|]].

Admiral Bahroo commissioned [[DyaRikku]] to create a "VTuber avatar":[https://twitter.com/dyarikku/status/1382609920512647169] featuring Samantha (3rd design) as a support avatar holding up the main avatar of Umeru. Due to technical issues with his commissioned computer his Live2D model was put offline.  After receiving a new commissioned computer from a new company he began streaming with Umeru alone until the beginning of March 2022 when he introduced his new VTuber avatar featuring Samantha's new updated 4th design.

h6. Standard designs

* 2nd Design (example: post #3712625): A panda hoodie with thighhighs
* 3rd Design (example: post #4290124): Blue sports crop top and pants under an off shoulder panda themed sweatshirt
* 4th Design (example: post #4953003): Panda [[bear girl|girl]] with [[multicolored hair|black and white hair]]

title: shiso-chan_(tawawa)
body:
The first character to be depicted in the [i][[Getsuyoubi no Tawawa]][/i] series. On the series' seventh anniversary, she was featured for the first time since her debut and christened as the "Originator" (始祖 [i]shiso[/i]).

Also nicknamed the "Founding 〇〇〇an" (始祖の巨〇), a pun on the name of the Founding Titan from [i][[Shingeki no Kyojin]][/i] (始祖の巨人), as the omission of the last word's second kanji leaves it open for reinterpretation as [i]kyonyuu[/i] (巨乳, "huge breasts"), referring to [i][[Getsuyoubi no Tawawa]][/i]'s basic premise of revolving around female characters with breasts that are [[large breasts|large]] at their smallest. Incidentally, the pun also works in English, as the "tit" in "titan" is slang for a woman's breast.

title: yasu_(umineko)
body:
[b]Major spoilers below.[/b]

Character from [[Umineko No Naku Koro Ni]].

[spoiler]Yasu, whose real name is Sayo Yasuda, was the child born from the incestuous relationship between [[Ushiromiya Kinzou]] and his daughter [[Ushiromiya Beatrice]]. Kinzo offered him to [[Ushiromiya Natsuhi]] to raise as her own child, but refused his offer and shoved the servant carrying Yasu off of a cliff, gravely injuring him. Even though Yasu survived, his sexual organs were damaged beyond surgical repair, and was raised as a female within the Fukuin House on Rokkenjima.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]He adopts many other personas that appear throughout the series, originating as imaginary friends to cope with the loneliness of being raised in the Fukuin House. [[Shannon (umineko)|]], [[Kanon (umineko)|]], and [[Beatrice (umineko)|]] are the result of this, and each personality went on to live as separate figures who fell in love with [[ushiromiya_george|George]], [[ushiromiya_jessica|Jessica]], and [[ushiromiya_battler|Battler]], respectively. Most furniture that appear in Umineko were created this way as well; [[Virgilia (umineko)|]] and [[Ronove (umineko)|]] were respectively based on [[Kumasawa Chiyo|]] and [[Ronoue Genji|]], his parental figures, and the Seven [[Stakes of Purgatory]] were based on the Fukuin household servants he worked with that picked on him mercilessly.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Due to being the last surviving child of Kinzo, he turns out to be the true heir of the Ushiromiya and inheritor of the gold promised for solving the epitaph. He is also behind the forgeries that are based off of the murders on Rokkenjima, and therefore Umineko's framing device. He later kills himself in [i]Requiem of the Golden Witch[/i] after surviving the murders and escaping with Battler.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]In an "ideal" existence in EP7, he is accepted by Natsuhi and later grows up to be [[Ushiromiya Lion]]. In EP5, he is known as "The Man from 19 Years Ago", a form of Sayo whose resentment towards his family took over all aspects of life. As this persona, Battler passed on harassing phonecalls to Natsuhi, attempting to implicate her as the killer on Rokkenjima, from a script which Sayo wrote.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]The name "Yasu" is derived the infamous "Yasu was the culprit" meme from [[Portopia Renzoku Satsujin Jiken]] ([i]The Portopia Serial Murder Case[/i]); in which it's revealed that the killer is Yasuhiro Mano, the player character's assistant who speaks and acts for him.[/spoiler]

The Angel of Adoration of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].

One of the First Twelve who govern the world. Refers to [[Kai (akuaya)|]] and [[Tis (akuaya)|]] as sons, showering them with affection.

He is an [[androgynous]] [[angel]] with [[long hair|long]] [[multicolored hair|pink and white hair]] and [[yellow eyes]]. Due to his angelic roots he has a [[halo]].

title: oscar_(akuaya)
body:
The Valiant Swordsman of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].

One of the best swordsmen of the Imperial Army, surpassing even [[demon|devils]]. Behind his brilliance he hides an indelible past.

He has [[red hair]] and [[green eyes]]. His [[sword]] is usually somewhere around him alongside the [[tattoo]] on his arm.

title: eric_(akuaya)
body:
The Melancholic Loyalist of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].

A young man who serves as adjutant of [[Claude (akuaya)|Claude's]] unit, despite his youth. Birth into an elite family has given him much to anguish over.

He has [[black hair]] and usually wears a [[hat]]. His eyes are [[blue]].

title: claude_(akuaya)
body:
The Beautiful Commander of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].

Of the Aquilegian Imperial line, Claude is adorned with harsh words. Serves as commander of the Imperial Army while never revealing true intentions to anyone.

He has [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. Usually has a sheathed [[sword]], although it isn't shown too often.

title: fiori_(akuaya)
body:
The Magnificent Princess of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].
 
[[Princess]] from a neighboring country, possessing both prettiness and thorns. Firori's relationship with the [[demon|devil]] is fraught with secrets.

She has [[blonde hair]] and usually wears a [[tiara]]. Her eyes are [[blue eyes|blue]].

title: dia_(akuaya)
body:
The Devil Prince of [[Akuma Ouji to Ayatsuri Ningyou]].
 
A boy who has become [[demon|devil]], spending eternity in nothingness. Once beloved as the [[prince]] of this land, he now exists by consuming the souls of men.

He has [[multicolored hair|white and black hair]] and typically wears a [[crown]]. Due to his [[heterochromia]], his left eye is [[red eyes|red]] and his right is [[blue eyes|blue]].

title: experimental_model_1_submachine_gun
body: The Experimental Model 1 Submachine gun is an 8mm submachine gun designed by Kijiro Nambu. Its most unusual feature is that its pistol grip doubles as the magazine well but due to the magazine's curvature, the grip is angled towards the muzzle in an awkward way. Design work was carried on with the The Experimental Model 2 Submachine gun, which used a more conventional layout.

An [[elf]] in [[Lord of Heroes]]. 

She has multiple designs that vary depending on the element she uses:
* [[Lucilicca La'Elaya (Dark)|Dark]], her default element, in which she has [[blonde hair]] and [[purple eyes]]
* [[Lucilicca La'Elaya (Earth)|Earth]], in which she has [[black hair]] and [[grey eyes]]
* [[Lucilicca La'Elaya (Water)|Water]], in which she has [[blue hair]] and [[grey eyes]]
* [[Lucilicca La'Elaya (Fire)|Fire]], in which she has [[red hair]] and [[green eyes]]
* [[Lucilicca La'Elaya (Light)|Light]], in which she has [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]]
other_names: ルシリカ・レヴォスカヤ
